\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 TWO-AIRPORT AIRLINE ON-TIME PERFORMANCE DATA DICTIONARY\
--------------------------------------------------\
\
YEAR\
  Four-digit year the flight occurred (e.g., 2024).\
\
MONTH\
  Numeric month (1\'9612). Some records may contain invalid values for testing.\
\
DAY_OF_MONTH\
  Day of the month (1\'9631). Not all values are valid calendar days.\
\
OP_UNIQUE_CARRIER\
  Two-letter airline code (e.g., AA, DL, UA, WN).\
  Some rows intentionally have missing carrier codes.\
\
ORIGIN\
  Origin airport code. In this dataset, CLT or ATL.\
\
DEST\
  Destination airport code (e.g., JFK, ORD).\
  Some rows may have missing destination values.\
\
DEP_DELAY\
  Departure delay in minutes.\
  Negative values indicate early departure.\
  Empty values indicate missing data.\
\
ARR_DELAY\
  Arrival delay in minutes.\
  Negative values indicate early arrival.\
  An arrival delay of 15 minutes or more is considered late.\
\
CANCELLED\
  Indicates whether the flight was cancelled.\
  0 = Not cancelled, 1 = Cancelled.\
  Cancelled flights may not have delay values.\
\
DATA QUALITY NOTES\
  - The dataset intentionally includes missing, invalid, and malformed rows.\
  - Students are expected to detect and handle data quality issues.\
  - Not all rows should be assumed valid.\
